From: "github-actions[bot]" <github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Mar 2026 22:25:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] docs: fix inconsistencies in documentation folder

- Replace `pnpm build --filter` with `pnpm turbo build --filter` across
  all docs (linting.md, Quickstart-on-how-to-write-tests.md,
  RLC-Swagger-quickstart.md, steps-after-generations.md,
  writing-performance-tests.md). The turbo-based command is required to
  correctly build a package and all its local dependencies via Turborepo.

- Replace `pnpm update` with `pnpm install` in RLC-Swagger-quickstart.md
  and steps-after-generations.md; `pnpm update` upgrades versions in the
  lockfile, while `pnpm install` is the correct command to refresh
  workspace dependencies.

- Replace `pnpm -F {./}... build` with `npx turbo build` in
  golden-testing-commands.md to use the Turborepo-native command
  recommended in CONTRIBUTING.md.

- Replace all `npm run test:*`, `npm run unit-test:*`,
  `npm run integration-test:*`, and `npm run perf-test:*` with their
  `pnpm run` equivalents in golden-testing-commands.md and
  writing-performance-tests.md. This repo enforces pnpm as the package
  manager.

- Update test code examples in Quickstart-on-how-to-write-tests.md to
  use the current vitest framework instead of the now-replaced mocha/chai:
  - Remove `import { Context } from "mocha"` (two occurrences)
  - Remove `import { assert } from "chai"`
  - Import `TestInfo` from `@azure-tools/test-recorder` for the
    recordedClient helper parameter type
  - Use `beforeEach(async (ctx) =>` / `new Recorder(ctx)` vitest pattern
    instead of `beforeEach(async function (this: Context)` /
    `new Recorder(this.currentTest)`
  - Import test utilities (assert, describe, it, beforeEach, afterEach)
    from `"vitest"`
  - Add `.js` extensions to local imports per ESM requirements

- Replace deprecated `dev-tool customization apply-v2` with
  `dev-tool customization apply` in migrating-to-typespec.md. The
  apply-v2 command emits a deprecation warning and delegates to apply.

- Replace `npm run generate:client`, `npm run build`, `npm run test`
  user-facing shell commands with `pnpm run` equivalents in
  migrating-to-typespec.md.

- Fix `npm install -g @pnpm` to `npm install -g pnpm` in
  Generate-code-from-TypeSpec.md; `@pnpm` is not a valid npm package.

- Fix missing path separator in resolve-pnpm-lock-merge-conflict.md:
  `git add `git rev-parse --show-toplevel`pnpm-lock.yaml` was missing
  the `/` between the directory and filename.

- Update example Node.js versions from "12,14" (both EOL) to "20,22"
  in run-your-azure-ts-js-samples-with-multiple-node-versions.md.

- Update stale hardcoded commit-SHA link to storage perf-tests in
  writing-performance-tests.md to point to the current main branch and
  correct path (`sdk/storage/storage-blob-perf-tests/README.md`).

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
